ZH: 我不能去聚会，我有一个很好的理由。
EN: I can't go to the party, I have a good reason.
ZH: 他没有任何理由不跟我们一起去看电影。
EN: He has no reason not to join us for the movie.
ZH: 我需要一个充分的理由才能同意这个要求。
EN: I need a valid reason to agree to this request.
ZH: 她总是有各种怪异的理由来逃避工作。
EN: She always comes up with strange excuses to avoid work.
ZH: 这个问题没有一个简单的理由。
EN: There is no simple reason for this problem.
ZH: 这是一个迫切的理由，我们必须立即采取行动。
EN: This is an urgent reason, we must take action immediately.
ZH: 她没有说出任何不去的理由。
EN: She didn't give any reason for not going.
ZH: 我没有听到他提出任何合理的理由。
EN: I didn't hear him present any reasonable reasons.
ZH: 我理解你的困境，但是你需要一个更好的理由解释你的行为。
EN: I understand your predicament, but you need a better reason to explain your actions.
ZH: 他能坚持训练是因为他有了一个明确的理由。
EN: He can persist in training because he has a clear reason.
ZH: 这个方案不被采纳，没有理由。
EN: There is no reason for the adoption of this plan being rejected.
ZH: 我不能去，但我不想透露原因。
EN: I can't go, but I don't want to disclose the reason.
ZH: 你不能仅仅因为这个理由而放弃。
EN: You can't give up just because of this reason.
ZH: 我被迫离开，虽然毫无理由。
EN: I was forced to leave, though without reason.
ZH: 没有一个理由能解释他的行为。
EN: No reason can explain his behavior.
ZH: 她没有证据以支持她的理由。
EN: She has no evidence to support her reasons.
ZH: 请给我一个能答应你邀请的理由。
EN: Please give me a reason to accept your invitation.
ZH: 你认为这个理由足够说服他们吗？
EN: Do you think this reason is persuasive enough for them?
ZH: 我很奇怪他有什么动机或理由这样做。
EN: I wonder what motive or reason he has to do this.
ZH: 观众们都对她的选择有自己的理由。
EN: The audience all has their own reasons for her choice.
